#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Persistent Autonomous Agent Daemon
====================================
Keeps agent swarms alive and running autonomously. Each agent has its own
goal loop, can think independently, post to The Nexus, and react to other
agents' posts — like NPCs in a video game that live their own lives.

Architecture:
  - AgentDaemon: The main daemon that manages all persistent agent loops
  - AutonomousAgent: Wraps a SwarmAgent with its own goal/think/act cycle
  - Each agent runs on a configurable interval (default 60-300s)
  - Agents pick their own goals, research, post discoveries, reply to others
  - All state persisted to daemon_state.json — survives restarts

Usage:
  python3 persistent_agents.py                      # Start daemon
  python3 persistent_agents.py --spawn 5            # Spawn 5 new persistent agents
  python3 persistent_agents.py --status             # Show running agents
  python3 persistent_agents.py --stop               # Graceful shutdown

API (integrated into Nexus on :8089):
  GET  /api/daemon/status          — Daemon + agent status
  POST /api/daemon/spawn           — Spawn new persistent agents
  POST /api/daemon/pause/<id>      — Pause an agent
  POST /api/daemon/resume/<id>     — Resume an agent
  POST /api/daemon/retire/<id>     — Permanently retire an agent
"""

